-- GE Capital Hires Ryan Zanin as Chief Risk Officer to Succeed Jim Colica
-- Craig Trudell
-- 2010-07-01T20:21:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/ge-capital-hires-ryan-zanin-as-chief-risk-officer-to-succeed-jim-colica.html

          
          
             GE Capital, the finance arm of
 General Electric Co. , hired  Ryan Zanin  as chief risk officer.  
 Zanin, 47, succeeds  Jim Colica , 62, who is retiring after
27 years at the company, GE said today in a statement
distributed by Business Wire. Zanin most recently was chief risk
officer for corporate credit at  Wells Fargo & Co . Before Wells
Fargo, he worked at  Deutsche Bank AG  for 14 years, according to
the statement. The position change is effective July 19, GE
Capital spokesman  Russel Wilkerson  said.  
